{"ID":270297, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"297\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs296.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs298.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 297<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">forbid any man leaving just as we are going to close the meeting. He is no gentleman who will do\n  it. I don&rsquo;t care who does it, even if it were the king of England. I forbid it. (April 16, 1843.) DHC\n  5:360-363.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Salvation Through Knowledge<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">It is not wisdom that we should have all knowledge at once presented before us;<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> but that we\n  should have a little at a time;<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> then we can comprehend it. President Smith then read the 2nd Epistle\n  of Peter, 1st chapter, 16th to last verses,<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> and dwelt upon the 19th verse<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> with some remarks.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Add to your faith knowledge,<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> etc. The principle of knowledge is the principle of salvation.<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span>\n  This principle can be comprehended by the faithful and diligent;<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> and every one that does not obtain\n  knowledge sufficient to be saved will be condemned.<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> The principle of salvation is given us through\n  the knowledge<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> of Jesus Christ.<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Salvation Is to Triumph over Enemies<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">Salvation<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> is nothing more nor less than to triumph over all<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> our enemies<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> and put them under\n  our feet. And when we have power to put all enemies under our feet<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> in this world, and a knowledge\n  to triumph over all evil spirits<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> in the world to come, then we are saved, as in the case of Jesus, who\n  was to reign until He had put all enemies under His feet,<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> and the last enemy was death.<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">No Salvation Without a Tabernacle<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">Perhaps there are principles here that few men have thought of. No person can have this\n  salvation except through a tabernacle.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Now, in this world, mankind are naturally selfish,<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> ambitious<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> and striving to excel one above\n  another;<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> yet some are willing to build up others as well as themselves.<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> So in the other world there\n  are a variety of spirits. Some seek to excel.<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span> And this was the case with Lucifer when he fell.<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span> He\n  sought for things which were unlawful.<span class=\"footRef\">24<\/span> Hence he was sent down,<span class=\"footRef\">25<\/span> and it is said he drew many\n  away with him;<span class=\"footRef\">26<\/span> and the greatness of his punishment is that he shall not have a tabernacle.<span class=\"footRef\">27<\/span> This\n  is his punishment. So the devil, thinking to thwart the decree of God,<span class=\"footRef\">28<\/span> by going up and down in the\n  earth,<span class=\"footRef\">29<\/span> seeking whom he<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109445\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109445)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109445)\">1 Cor. 3:2<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110164\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110164)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110164)\">Heb. 5:12<\/a><\/span>;\n  